cs:
    a skos:ConceptScheme ;
    owl:versionIRI :3 ;
    skos:definition """The GA Vocabulary Register applies a sub-set of concepts from the Australian and New Zealand Fields of Research (FoR) to improve search of the register as it grows. 

The FoR classification allows research and development activity to be categorised according to the methodology used in the research and development activity, rather than the activity of the unit performing the research and development or the purpose of the research and development activity. The categories in the classification include major fields and related sub-fields of research and emerging areas of study investigated by businesses, universities, tertiary institutions, national research institutions and other organisations. This classification allows the categorisation of fields of research activity within Australia and New Zealand."""@en ;
    skos:hasTopConcept
        :37 ,
        :370509 ,
        :370510 ,
        :44 ,
        :46 ;
    skos:historyNote "This vocabulary is drawn from the Australian and New Zealand Research Classification 2020: Fields of Research. Definitions are drawn from various sources as referenced in the History Notes."@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "GA Vocabulary Register - Themes"@en ;
